<book xml:id="book.hackmagic" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
 <title>Functions Special-Cased by the type checker</title>

 <preface xml:id="intro.hackmagic">
  &reftitle.intro;
  <note>
   <para>
    These functions are an HHVM specific extension, part of the Hack language.
   </para>
  </note>
  <para>
   These functions are provided by default by the runtime in Hack code, but are also treated specially by the type checker during static analysis time (or, in the case of <function>invariant_callback_register</function>, are inextricably linked with those which are).
  </para>
  <para>
   In PHP code, these functions are available in the <literal>HH</literal> namespace.
  </para>
 </preface>

